## Step 3 — THE FAST-CHAIN CALL (one JS call per question)

**Critical rule: fire this as ONE `javascript_tool` call. Never split into
separate calls for select, confidence, and next.**

```javascript
(async () => {
  const d = ms => new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, ms));

  function clickOpt(t) {
    const m = [...document.querySelectorAll('label.form-check-label')]
      .find(l => l.innerText.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()));
    if (m) { const i = m.querySelector('input'); if (i) i.click(); else m.click(); }
  }

  // 1. SELECT ANSWER(S)
  clickOpt('<partial text of correct answer>');
  await d(150);
  // clickOpt('<second answer if multiple-select>');
  // await d(150);

  // 2. HIGH CONFIDENCE
  [...document.querySelectorAll('button')]
    .find(b => b.innerText.trim().toLowerCase() === 'high')?.click();
  await d(1800);

  // 3. NEXT QUESTION
  [...document.querySelectorAll('button')]
    .find(b => b.innerText.trim().toLowerCase().includes('next'))?.click();
  await d(1200);

  // 4. RETURN PROGRESS + NEXT QUESTION BODY
  return JSON.stringify({
    progress: document.querySelector('[class*="concept"]')?.innerText?.trim(),
    body:     document.body.innerText.substring(0, 1800)
  });
})()
```

**Timing — do not reduce these:**

| Pause | Duration | Why |
|-------|----------|-----|
| Between multi-select clicks | 150 ms | React state update |
| After High confidence click | 1800 ms | Answer-feedback animation |
| After Next click | 1200 ms | Next question DOM load |

---

## Step 4 — Loop until target reached

After each fast-chain call:
1. Parse `progress` — e.g. `"13 of 20 Concepts completed"`
2. If `completed >= target` → **stop and output the study key**
3. Otherwise → read next question from `body`, determine answer, fire next
   fast-chain call immediately

**Never take a screenshot between questions.**
**Never use `get_page_text` between questions.**
Read everything from the `body` string returned by the previous JS call.

